data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

In .NET 10, the Cosmos DB provider already didn't natively support sync operations — it performed **sync-over-async** under the hood, gated behind an opt-in (e.g., `ConfigureWarnings(w => w.Ignore(CosmosEventId.SyncNotSupported))`).

**In .NET 11 (EF Core 11), that opt-in is removed.** Synchronous LINQ operators and `SaveChanges()` on the Cosmos provider now throw `InvalidOperationException` unconditionally. There is no workaround — you **must** go async.

### Every call in your repo breaks:

| Sync (breaks) | Async (replacement) |
|---|---|
| `.ToList()` | `.ToListAsync()` |
| `.First(...)` | `.FirstAsync(...)` |
| `.Count()` | `.CountAsync()` |
| `.SaveChanges()` | `.SaveChangesAsync()` |

### Migrated code

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

This change will cascade — all callers must be updated to `await` the new async signatures.
